        "position": 1,
        "title": "Good Quality",
        "text": "This crate is exactly as described. It is easy to setup. Just unfold, the top is stored in the very bottom for shipping, screw in the 4 screws, and 2 bolts for the top. So easy! Very sturdy. I’ve had mine for a week now, and so far, my escape artist hasn’t been able to get out. I purchased the 42 inch size. I do put the plastic tray on top of the wire floor, instead or all the way at the bottom. My dog is house broken and I don’t think that wire bottom is all that safe to stand on. All the crates I looked at had it though. It works great with the tray on top of the wire, fits nice and tight. My only complaint is the wheels, they leave black marks on the floor! I covered them with tape. Very worth the money.",
