        "position": 6,
        "title": "Perfect for separation anxiety fur babies!",
        "text": "We have a pitbull with separation anxiety. She has ate one of our doors. She has ate through wire crates when being in them for an hour at most. So we needed something durable enough to be able to kennel her when we have guests or deliveries without more damage being done. Needles to say she loves it. While we’re home we don’t kennel her but leave it open and she goes in herself especially after we put her new bed in there. She has not chewed through it either. It was super easy to assemble as well. Durable and the wheels make it easy to move from room to room. We got it while on sale but worth the extra money. It’s roomy for her to stand on all fours and move around. Again we have had it since December and it’s still working as intended and standing strong! She has yet to chew or escape!",
